rComments: Awesome professor! I loved physiology story time. Always willing to stay after class to answer questions. Clearly loves physiology and teaches it exceptionally well! Lots of great practical examples in class.  Explains difficult concepts well, but makes it fun!!  Wish she taught more classes.

Dr. Reed is very nice and really cares about her student. However her exams were  hard and she gave a lot of readings (articles) that we had to memorize by heart, which in my opinion is completely useless. If you do not like reading, do not take this class.  Do not recommend taking special topics with her as an elective to boost your GPA.

If you want a professor who cares A LOT about her students and goes the extra mile to make sure you learn A LOT and prepares you for future courses in the health field - take a course with Dr. Reed!! She is amazing, but tough! I really enjoyed her course, super interesting and practical.  Great professor, physiology wizz.

I took this course last year and did fine.  I don't know what the other posters are complaining about - they must not have gone to lectures.  If you go to class and pay attention, you'll do fine.  Very fair prof, always willing to help if you go to office hours or send emails with questions.
Excellent prof!  Very helpful and always willing to spend extra time after class.  Extremely passionate and knowledgeable about the subject.  I will definitely take other classes taught by Dr. Reed.
Great prof. Very knowledgeable and helpful!

The exam was ridiculous... cumulative over 1000 slides, with no idea of anything not to study. She seems to purposely make the class extremely challenging. I have never heard anyone take this class that has had this much work for a nutrition class. DO NOT TAKE
Nice person, but a ridiculous amount of information/numbers needed to be memorized for midterms and the final. 1000 slides on the final, are you kidding me?
Makes the course a lot harder then it should be. I would not recommend her. If you have an option for another prof in this course, take it.
